Four people died and two others injured after the vehicle they were traveling in veered off the road and rolled several times at Don Bosco area in Embu. The six were traveling from Embu to Kiritiri town for a house warming party when the pick-up left Embu –Kiritiri road and rolled several times. Embu West Deputy Police boss Ziro Arome on Tuesday said two of the victims, the driver, Mr David Njiru, and Mr Anthony Njue, died on the spot in the noon crash. Four other passengers were rushed to Tenri Children’s Hospital, where two others succumbed to their injuries. Mr Arome said one of those admitted to the private hospital was unconscious while the other, Mr Erick Maina, sustained slight injuries on the forehead and hands. Their vehicle was towed to Embu Police Station.  